ite tweet |user=ESPN |number=1209463737058562048 |date=December 24, 2019 |title=IT'S HAPPENING #TheLastDance | Coming in June}}</ref>\n| first_aired          = <!-- {{Start date|YYYY|MM|DD}} -->\n| related              = ''[[30 for 30]]''\n| website              = https://www.espn.com/watch/series/0514c1ad-efd1-4d3a-ad82-41ca579a94a2/30-for-30-spotlight\n}}\n\n'''''The Last Dance''''' is a 2020 [[Television documentary|sports documentary]] miniseries focusing on the  [[1997\u201398 Chicago Bulls season|1997\u201398]] [[Chicago Bulls]]. The series will feature film from a crew that had all-access pass to the Bulls during the [[National Basketball Association]] (NBA) [[1997-98 NBA season|season]]. The 10-part miniseries<ref name=\"maxim\">{{cite news |title=ESPN Documentary 'The Last Dance' About Michael Jordan and the Chicago Bulls, Gets a New Trailer |url=https://www.maxim.com/sports/the-last-dance-michael-jackson-bulls-documentary-2019-12 |accessdate=January 4, 2020 |publisher=[[Maxim (magazine)|Maxim]] |date=December 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191228080305/https://www.maxim.com/sports/the-last-dance-michael-jackson-bulls-documentary-2019-12 |archive-date=December 28, 2019 |url-status=live }}</ref> was announced by [[ESPN]] in 2018 with an official trailer released on December 24, 2019.<ref name=\"thewrap\">{{cite news |last1=Welk |first1=Brian |title='The Last Dance' Trailer: Barack Obama, Justin Timberlake Reflect on Legend of Michael Jordan and '90s Chicago Bulls (Video) |url=https://www.thewrap.com/the-last-dance-trailer-barack-obama-justin-timberlake-reflect-on-legend-of-michael-jordan-and-90s-chicago-bulls-video/ |accessdate=January 4, 2020 |publisher=[[TheWrap]] |date=December 24, 2019 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200103131131/https://www.thewrap.com/the-last-dance-trailer-barack-obama-justin-timberlake-reflect-on-legend-of-michael-jordan-and-90s-chicago-bulls-video/ |archive-date=January 3, 2020 |url-status=live }}</ref><ref name=\"espntwitter\" />\n\n== Premise ==\nThe series will focus on the [[1997\u201398 Chicago Bulls season]] and [[Michael Jordan]]'s final season with the Bulls.<ref name=\"espnpressrelease\">{{cite press release |last=Christie |first=Jennifer |date=May 18, 2018 |title=ESPN Films, Netflix Announce Multi-Part Documentary The Last Dance featuring Michael Jordan |url=https://espnpressroom.com/us/press-releases/2018/05/espn-films-and-netflix-announce-multi-part-documentary-the-last-dance-featuring-michael-jordan/ |location=New York, New York |publisher=[[ESPN]] |agency= |access-date=January 4, 2020 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20191121121814/https://espnpressroom.com/us/press-releases/2018/05/espn-films-and-netflix-announce-multi-part-documentary-the-last-dance-featuring-michael-jordan/ |archive-date=November 21, 2019 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n{{Episode table| background=8B0000 |overall=5 |title=23 |director=20 |writer=20 |airdate=18 |viewers=10 |country=U.S. |episodes=\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 1\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Jason Hehir\n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|19}}<ref name=\"NBA.com\" />\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 8B0000\n |Viewers         = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 2\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Jason Hehir\n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|19}}<ref name=\"NBA.com\" />\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 8B0000\n |Viewers         = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 3\n |Title          = \n |DirectedBy      = Jason Hehir\n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|26}}<ref name=\"NBA.com\" />\n |ShortSummary    = \n |LineColor       = 8B0000\n |Viewers         = \n}}\n{{Episode list\n |EpisodeNumber   = 4\n |Title           = \n |DirectedBy      = Jason Hehir\n |WrittenBy       = \n |OriginalAirDate = {{Start date|2020|4|26}}<ref name=\"NBA.com\" />\n |ShortSumm