onto a small perspex like screen just in front of the main windscreen area in front of the driver. It also contains a distance alert, which warns the driver if he or she is too close to the car in front. It also displays details for cruise control or the speed limiter.\n\n===Hybrid Version===\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 HYbrid4 \u2013 Frontansicht, 30. August 2012, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg|thumb|right|Peugeot 3008 HYbrid4]]\nThe Peugeot 3008 [[PSA HYbrid4|HYbrid4]] was launched in February 2012, and is the world's first mass production diesel electric hybrid.<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2012\"/><ref>{{cite news|title=Peugeot's hybrid|url=http://www.independent.ie/lifestyle/motoring/peugeots-hybrid-2996208.html|accessdate=25 January 2012|newspaper=Sunday Independent|date=22 January 2012}}</ref>\n\nThe [[Crossover (automobile)|crossover]] hybrid has four different operating modes: Auto (the electronics automatically control the entire system), [[Zero Emission Vehicle|ZEV]] ([[all-electric mode|all electric]]), [[four wheel drive]] mode (4WD) and sport (higher engine speeds than normal mode). A 200v [[nickel-metal hydride]] (Ni-MH) [[battery pack]] is located in the rear.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.greencarcongress.com/2010/08/3008-20100824.html#more|title=Peugeot\u2019s Diesel 3008 Hybrid4|publisher=[[Green Car Congress]]|date=24 August 2010|accessdate=24 August 2010}}</ref>\n\n=== Safety ===\n{{Euro NCAP\n|year=2009\n|align=left\n|overall_stars=5\n|description=5 door LHD Hatchback\n|reference_name=EuroNCAP361\n|reference_code=361\n|adult_points=31\n|adult_percent=86\n|child_points=40\n|child_percent=81\n|pedestrian_points=11\n|pedestrian_percent=31\n|safety_points=7\n|safety_percent=97}}  \n{{clear}}\n\n=== Sales and production figures ===\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Worldwide production\n! Worldwide sales\n! Notes\n|-\n|2008\n|{{TBA}}\n| align=\"center\" |400<ref name=\"PSA sales figures\">{{cite web|url=http://www.psa-peugeot-citroen.com/en/fonctionnelle/automobiles.php |title=PSA |publisher=Psa-peugeot-citroen.com |date=30 June 2010 |accessdate=4 December 2010 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101206165618/http://www.psa-peugeot-citroen.com/en/fonctionnelle/automobiles.php |archivedate= 6 December 2010 }}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|2009\n| align=\"center\" |64,700<ref name=\"Engine specs from PSA Peugeot Citro\u00ebn\"/>\n| align=\"center\" |59,500<ref name=\"PSA sales figures\"/>\n|\n|-\n|2010\n| align=\"center\" |132,500<ref name=\"Engine specs from PSA Peugeot Citro\u00ebn\"/>\n| align=\"center\" |129,600<ref name=\"Engine specs from PSA Peugeot Citro\u00ebn\">{{cite web|title=Engine specs from PSA Peugeot Citro\u00ebn|url=http://www.info-financiere.fr/upload/BWR/8888/01/FCBWR066301_20110422.pdf|work=Creator and designer|publisher=PSA Peugeot Citro\u00ebn|accessdate=22 November 2012}}</ref>\n|\n|-\n|2011\n| align=\"center\" |139,827<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2012\"/>\n| align=\"center\" |134,951<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2012\">{{cite web|title=PSA Annual Report 2012|url=http://annualreport.psa-peugeot-citroen.com/wp-content/themes/psa/pdf/pdf/PSA-2012-03_memento_en.pdf|work=Car manufacturers|publisher=PSA|accessdate=4 April 2013}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n|Total production reaches 337,447 units.<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2012\"/>\n|-\n|2012\n| align=\"center\" |104,000<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2013\">{{cite journal|title=Memento Mars 2013|date=21 February 2013|page=50|url=http://www.psa-peugeot-citroen.com/fr/pagebuilder/downloadpackage/2293?pid=-1|publisher=PSA Peugeot Citro\u00ebn|accessdate=31 July 2013|language=fr}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n| align=\"center\" |108,300<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2013\"/>\n|Total production reaches 441,500 units.<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2013\"/>\n|}\n\n===Global version===\n'''Pre-facelift styling'''\n<gallery widths=\"200\" perrow=\"4\">\nFile:2014 Peugeot 3008 (T8 MY13) Allure HDi wagon (2015-07-16) 01.jpg|Front\nFile:2014 Peugeot 3008 (T8 MY13) Allure HDi wagon (2015-07-16) 02.jpg|Rear\n</gallery>\n\n'''Facelift styling'''\n<gallery widths=\"200\" perrow=\"4\">\nFile:Peugeot 3008 Business-Line (Facelift) \u2013 Frontansicht, 30. November 2014, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg|Front\nFile:Peugeot 3008 Business-Line (Facelift) \u2013 Heckansicht, 30. November 2014, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg|Rear\n</gallery>\n\n===Chinese version===\n'''Pre-facelift styling'''\n<gallery widths=\"200\" perrow=\"2\">\nFile:Peugeot 3008 CN 3 China 2014-04-16.jpg|Front\nFile:Peugeot 3008 CN 002 China 2013-03-04.jpg|Rear\n</gallery>\n\n'''Facelift styling'''\n<gallery widths=\"200\" perrow=\"2\">\nFile:Peugeot 3008 A facelift.jpg|Front\nFile:Peugeot 3008 A facelift rear.jpg|Rear\n</gallery>\n\n=={{Anchor|2}}Second generation (2016\u2013present)==\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = Peugeot 3008 II\n| image = Peugeot 3008 BlueHDi 180 EAT8 GT (II) \u2013 Frontansicht (1), 25. November 2018, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg\n| caption = \n| manufacturer = Peugeot\n| aka = Peugeot 4008 (China)\n| production = 2016\u2013present\n| assembly = France: [[Sochaux]]<br/>China: [[Chengdu]]<br/>Namibia: [[Walvis Bay]]<br/>Malaysia: [[Gurun, Kedah|Gurun]] ([[Naza Automotive Manufacturing#Peugeot / DS|NAM]])\n| designer = \n| class = [[Compact car|Compact]] [[crossover SUV]] ([[C-segment|C]])\n| body_style = 5-door [[SUV]]\n| platform = [[PSA EMP2 platform]]\n| related = [[Opel Grandland X]]<br />[[Citro\u00ebn C5 Aircross]]<br />[[Peugeot 5008#Second Generation (2017\u2013present)|Peugeot 5008 II]]<br>[[DS 7 Crossback]]\n| layout = [[FF layout]]\n| engine = 1.2 L Puretech 130<br />1.6 L [[Prince engine|PSA-EP6CDT THP 165]]<br />1.6 L BlueHDi 100<br />1.6 L BlueHDi 120<br />2.0 L BlueHDi 150<br />2.0 L BlueHDi 180\n| transmission = 5-speed Manual (BVM5)<br />6-speed manual (6SMT)(BVM6)<br />6-speed automatic (EAT6)\n| wheelbase = {{convert|2675|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<br>{{convert|2730|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (China & ASEAN)\n| length = {{convert|4450|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}<br>{{convert|4510|mm|in|1|abbr=on}} (China & ASEAN)\n| width = {{convert|1840|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| height = {{convert|1620|mm|in|1|abbr=on}}\n| weight = \n| predecessor = Peugeot 3008 (first generation)<br>[[Peugeot 4008]]\n| successor = \n}}\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 BlueHDi 180 EAT8 GT (II) \u2013 Heckansicht (1), 25. November 2018, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg|thumb|left|Rear view]]\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 THP 165 EAT6 Allure GT-Line (II) \u2013 Innenraum, 20. September 2017, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg|thumb|left|Interior]]\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 Hybrid4, Paris Motor Show 2018, IMG 0227.jpg|thumb|left|Peugeot 3008 Hybrid4]]\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 Hybrid4, Paris Motor Show 2018, IMG 0691.jpg|thumb|left|Rear view]]\n\nA second generation 3008 was announced by [[Peugeot]] in May 2016, and was first presented to the public at the [[2016 Paris Motor Show|Paris Motor Show]] in September 2016. Its design allows the vehicle to come into contention with large competitors in the C segment market of SUVs, which has been a prominent market in the past years.\n\nIt features [[Peugeot]]'s new iCockpit, which is an improved design compared to the current iCockpit featured in the [[Peugeot 208]], [[Peugeot 2008]] and [[Peugeot 308]]. The second generation was introduced on 23 May 2016.\n\nFeatures include an eight-inch touch screen to the centre console, a 12.3-inch customisable heads up display, and the small style steering wheel, which has become standard in all current models of [[Peugeot]].\n\nProduction started in 2016, with sales starting in January 2017. 100,000 orders were made in Europe between October 2016 and March 2017, half of them were made by people who did not own a Peugeot.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/societes/2017/03/01/20005-20170301ARTFIG00318-peugeot-capitalise-sur-le-succes-du-nouveau-3008.php|title=Peugeot capitalise sur le succ\u00e8s du nouveau 3008|last=Egloff|first=Emmanuel|date=1 March 2017|work=Le Figaro|access-date=5 March 2017|language=fr-FR|issn=0182-5852}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n== Awards ==\n* [[European Car of the Year]] 2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.caroftheyear.org/winner/Peugeot/3008/2017_117/coty|title=Car of the Year 2017: Peugeot 3008, a winning formula \u2013 Car of the year|website=www.caroftheyear.org|access-date=6 March 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307045705/http://www.caroftheyear.org/winner/Peugeot/3008/2017_117/coty|archivedate=7 March 2017}}</ref>\n* ''[[Carbuyer|CarBuyer]]'' Car of the Year 2017<ref name=\"charterspeugeot.com\"/>\n* ''DieselCar Magazine'' Car of the Year 2017\n* ''DieselCar Magazine'' Best Medium SUV 2017\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Peugeot 3008}}\n\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101003141947/http://www.peugeot.co.uk/vehicles/peugeot-car-range/peugeot-3008/ Official UK 3008 website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110315083257/http://www.peugeot.co.uk/vehicles/peugeot-car-range/peugeot-3008-hybrid4/ Official 3008 HYbrid4 page]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SIhe5HnOiHI Peugeot 3008 Active 2.0HDI Exterior and Interior in Full 3D HD]\n*[https://www.perthcitypeugeot.com.au/news/5-reasons-to-choose-the-award-winning-new-peugeot-3008-suv-in-2019/ Benefits Of The Peugeot 3008]\n\n{{Peugeot}}\n{{Peugeot timeline 1980 to date}}\n\n[[Category:Peugeot vehicles|3008]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2009]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2016]]\n[[Category:Compact sport utility vehicles]]\n[[Category:2000s cars]]\n[[Category:2010s cars]]\n[[Category:Cars of China]]\n[[Category:Plug-in hybrid vehicles]]\n", "text_old": "{{Redirect|3008|the future year \"3008\"|4th millennium}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = Peugeot 3008\n| image = Peugeot 3008 PureTech 130 Active (II) \u2013 Frontansicht, 7. Mai 2017, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg\n| caption = Second generation 3008\n| manufacturer = [[Peugeot]]\n| production = 2008\u2013present\n| class = [[Compact SUV|Compact]] [[crossover SUV]]\n| predecessor = [[Peugeot 4007]]<br/>[[Peugeot 4008]]\n| successor = \n}}\nThe '''Peugeot 3008''' is a [[compact SUV|compact]] [[crossover SUV]] unveiled by French automaker [[Peugeot]] in May 2008, and presented for the first time to the public in [[Dubrovnik, Croatia]]. It was launched in April 2009.<ref name=\"PSA Annual Report 2012\"/>\n\nDespite having had its styling criticised, the 3008 has been praised by automobile magazines. In January 2010, the British motoring magazine ''[[What Car?]]'' awarded it ''[[Car of the Year]]'' for 2010. It also was awarded 2010 [[Semperit Irish Car of the Year]] in Ireland. The 3008 followed up this award in 2018, by winning the [[Continental Irish Car of the Year]].\n\nIn 2016, [[Peugeot]] unveiled the new 3008, with the car being available as of January 2017. The car is due to be a new milestone for Peugeot, in its quest to become the highest selling range of vehicles in the industry. In November 2016, the new 3008 was awarded overall ''[[Carbuyer|CarBuyer]]'' \"Car of the Year\" 2017, as well as winning best in the category of SUVs.<ref name=\"charterspeugeot.com\">{{Cite news|url=https://www.charterspeugeot.com/news/new-3008-suv-wins-carbuyer-car-year-award/|title=New 3008 SUV wins CarBuyer Car of the Year Award \u2013 Charters Peugeot|newspaper=Charters Peugeot|language=en-GB|access-date=30 November 2016}}</ref>\n\n''Diesel Car Magazine'' awarded the 3008 the overall award of Car of the Year for 2017, as well as taking the honour of ''Best Medium SUV''.\n\nIn March 2017, the new 3008 won [[European Car of the Year]] 2017, by a jury of 58 motoring journalists from twenty two European countries. The award came the same day that the [[Groupe PSA|PSA Group]] announced a $2.3 billion deal to buy GM's [[Opel]] division. Opel's [[Opel Astra|Astra]] won the Car of the Year in 2016, reacted with these two awards within two years, the Peugeot Group CEO Jean-Philippe Imparato said, \"This is an alliance of winners\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://business.inquirer.net/225709/peugeot-3008-named-car-year-geneva-auto-show|title=Peugeot 3008 named 'Car of the Year' at Geneva auto show|last=Press|first=Associated|website=business.inquirer.net|language=en|access-date=6 March 2017}}</ref>\n\n=={{Anchor|1}}First generation (2008\u20132016)==\n{{Infobox automobile\n| name = Peugeot 3008 I\n| image = Peugeot 3008 China 2012-05-12.JPG\n| production = 2008\u20132016<br/>2013\u2013present (China)\n| assembly = France: [[Mulhouse]] ([[PSA Mulhouse Plant]])<br/>France: [[Sochaux]] ([[PSA Sochaux Plant]])<ref name=\"Engine specs from PSA Peugeot Citro\u00ebn\"/><br/>Argentina: [[El Palomar, Buenos Aires|El Palomar]] ([[Peugeot|PSA Argentina]])<br/>China: [[Wuhan]] ([[Dongfeng Peugeot-Citro\u00ebn|DPCA]])<br/>Malaysia: [[Gurun, Kedah|Gurun]] ([[Naza Automotive Manufacturing#Peugeot|NAM]])\n| class = [[Compact car|Compact]] [[crossover SUV]]\n| body_style = 5-door [[SUV]]\n| layout = [[Front-engine, front-wheel-drive layout|Front-engine, front-wheel-drive]] or [[Front-engine, four-wheel-drive layout|four-wheel-drive]]\n| platform = [[PSA PF2 platform]]\n| engine = 1.2&nbsp;L [[List of PSA engines#EB|EB e-THP]] [[Straight-three engine|I3]] ([[petrol engine|petrol]])<br />1.6&nbsp;L [[Prince engine|Prince]] [[straight-4|I4]] ([[petrol engine|petrol]])<br />1.6&nbsp;L [[Prince engine|Prince]] [[Turbocharger|THP]] [[straight-4|I4]] ([[petrol engine|petrol]])<br />1.6&nbsp;L ''[[Ford DLD engine#DLD-416|DV6 HDi]]'' [[straight-4|I4]] ([[diesel engine|diesel]])<br />2.0&nbsp;L ''[[PSA EW/DW engine#DW10|DW10 HDi]]'' [[straight-4|I4]] ([[diesel engine|diesel]])<br />2.0&nbsp;L ''[[PSA EW/DW engine#DW10|DW10 HDi]]'' [[straight-4|I4]] ([[diesel engine|diesel]]) with [[electric engine]] (HYbrid4)\n| transmission = 5-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]]<br />6-speed [[Manual transmission|manual]]<br />6-speed [[Automatic transmission|au