geot 3008 BlueHDi 180 EAT8 GT (II) \u2013 Heckansicht (1), 25. November 2018, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg|thumb|left|Rear view]]\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 THP 165 EAT6 Allure GT-Line (II) \u2013 Innenraum, 20. September 2017, D\u00fcsseldorf.jpg|thumb|left|Interior]]\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 Hybrid4, Paris Motor Show 2018, IMG 0227.jpg|thumb|left|Peugeot 3008 Hybrid4]]\n[[File:Peugeot 3008 Hybrid4, Paris Motor Show 2018, IMG 0691.jpg|thumb|left|Rear view]]\n\nA second generation 3008 was announced by [[Peugeot]] in May 2016, and was first presented to the public at the [[2016 Paris Motor Show|Paris Motor Show]] in September 2016. Its design allows the vehicle to come into contention with large competitors in the C segment market of SUVs, which has been a prominent market in the past years.\n\nIt features [[Peugeot]]'s new iCockpit, which is an improved design compared to the current iCockpit featured in the [[Peugeot 208]], [[Peugeot 2008]] and [[Peugeot 308]]. The second generation was introduced on 23 May 2016.\n\nFeatures include an eight-inch touch screen to the centre console, a 12.3-inch customisable heads up display, and the small style steering wheel, which has become standard in all current models of [[Peugeot]].\n\nProduction started in 2016, with sales starting in January 2017. 100,000 orders were made in Europe between October 2016 and March 2017, half of them were made by people who did not own a Peugeot.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.lefigaro.fr/societes/2017/03/01/20005-20170301ARTFIG00318-peugeot-capitalise-sur-le-succes-du-nouveau-3008.php|title=Peugeot capitalise sur le succ\u00e8s du nouveau 3008|last=Egloff|first=Emmanuel|date=1 March 2017|work=Le Figaro|access-date=5 March 2017|language=fr-FR|issn=0182-5852}}</ref>\n{{clear}}\n\n== Awards ==\n* [[European Car of the Year]] 2017<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.caroftheyear.org/winner/Peugeot/3008/2017_117/coty|title=Car of the Year 2017: Peugeot 3008, a winning formula \u2013 Car of the year|website=www.caroftheyear.org|access-date=6 March 2017|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170307045705/http://www.caroftheyear.org/winner/Peugeot/3008/2017_117/coty|archivedate=7 March 2017}}</ref>\n* ''[[Carbuyer|CarBuyer]]'' Car of the Year 2017<ref name=\"charterspeugeot.com\"/>\n* ''DieselCar Magazine'' Car of the Year 2017\n* ''DieselCar Magazine'' Best Medium SUV 2017\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category|Peugeot 3008}}\n\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20101003141947/http://www.peugeot.co.uk/vehicles/peugeot-car-range/peugeot-3008/ Official UK 3008 website]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20110315083257/http://www.peugeot.co.uk/vehicles/peugeot-car-range/peugeot-3008-hybrid4/ Official 3008 HYbrid4 page]\n*[https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=SIhe5HnOiHI Peugeot 3008 Active 2.0HDI Exterior and Interior in Full 3D HD]\n*[https://www.perthcitypeugeot.com.au/news/5-reasons-to-choose-the-award-winning-new-peugeot-3008-suv-in-2019/ Benefits Of The Peugeot 3008]\n\n{{Peugeot}}\n{{Peugeot timeline 1980 to date}}\n\n[[Category:Peugeot vehicles|3008]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2009]]\n[[Category:Cars introduced in 2016]]\n[[Category:Compact sport utility vehicles]]\n[[Category:2000s cars]]\n[[Category:2010s cars]]\n[[Category:Cars of China]]\n[[Category:Plug-in hybrid vehicles]]\n", "name_user": "2a00:23c6:e182:7800:1c3a:7804:c1ab:d2c4", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Peugeot_3008"}
